---
title: "/pr-review — Probabilistic Path"
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant H as Human
    participant A as Agent
    participant L01 as L01 Tooling
    participant HARN as L03 HARNESS
    participant GOV as L03 GOVERNANCE
    participant Obs as ObservabilityStack

    Note over H,Obs: L0-L1 — Human reads the diff. No agent. No HARNESS. No GOVERNANCE.
    H->>L01: PR queued in review backlog
    L01-->>H: Human reads diff, leaves comments (4-24 hours typical)

    Note over H,Obs: L2 — Agent-driven review with HARNESS + GOVERNANCE

    rect rgb(240, 240, 255)
        Note right of GOV: GOVERNANCE wraps the entire execution

        A->>GOV: governance.identity.register(agent_id, {team, permissions})
        GOV->>Obs: obs.tracer.start_span("governance-wrap")

        A->>GOV: governance.security.add_policy("repo-scope-check")
        A->>GOV: governance.security.add_policy("no-merge-policy")

        A->>GOV: governance.wrap(agent_id, action, harness_fn)
        activate GOV
        GOV->>GOV: identity.verify(agent_id)
        GOV->>GOV: security.enforce(action)
        GOV->>Obs: obs_stack.tracer.start_span("governance-wrap")
        GOV->>Obs: obs_stack.logger.info("Governance wrap started")
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note right of HARN: HARNESS orchestrates the agent execution

        GOV->>HARN: harness.run(input, "generate-review", constraints)
        activate HARN

        Note over HARN: 1. Context
        HARN->>L01: Read source files (file_paths)
        L01-->>HARN: file contents, ADRs, conventions

        Note over HARN: 2. Capability
        HARN->>HARN: Select model by change_type<br/>(routine → fast, security → thorough)

        Note over HARN: 3. Execution
        alt simulate mode
            HARN->>HARN: ast.parse() heuristic analysis
            HARN->>HARN: Pattern-based code review
        else live mode
            HARN->>HARN: Claude API generates structured review
        end

        Note over HARN: 4. Evaluation
        HARN->>HARN: Assess confidence, determine action<br/>(human-validates — agent does NOT merge)

        HARN-->>GOV: {components: {context, capability, execution, evaluation}}
        deactivate HARN
    end

    rect rgb(240, 240, 255)
        GOV->>GOV: observability.record(execution_event)
        GOV->>Obs: obs_stack.tracer.end_span("governance-wrap")
        GOV->>Obs: obs_stack.metrics.counter("governance_executions")
        GOV-->>A: governed_result {identity, security, result}
        deactivate GOV
    end

    A-->>H: Structured review with evidence trail<br/>Human validates and decides whether to merge

%% Flow (L0-L1):
%% (1) PR is opened. It sits in the review backlog.
%% (2) A human reviewer opens the diff, reads it, and leaves comments. Typical turnaround: 4-24 hours.
%% (3) No agent, no HARNESS, no GOVERNANCE. Pure manual process.
%%
%% Flow (L2):
%% (1) Agent registers its identity with GOVERNANCE (team scope, permissions: read + comment only).
%% (2) Two security policies are added: repo-scope-check (agent stays within its repo) and
%%     no-merge-policy (agent cannot merge — human approval required).
%% (3) Agent calls governance.wrap(), which verifies identity and enforces all policies before
%%     allowing execution. A trace span is opened.
%% (4) Inside the governance wrapper, HARNESS.run() is called with four phases:
%%     (a) Context — reads the source files, loads ADRs and team conventions from L01.
%%     (b) Capability — selects the review model/strategy based on change type
%%         (routine changes get a fast model, security changes get a thorough one).
%%     (c) Execution — in simulate mode, ast.parse() runs heuristic analysis on the actual code.
%%         In live mode, Claude API generates a structured review with categorized findings.
%%     (d) Evaluation — assesses confidence. The action is always "human-validates" at L2.
%%         The agent does NOT merge.
%% (5) HARNESS returns the structured result (context, capability, execution, evaluation) to GOVERNANCE.
%% (6) GOVERNANCE records the execution event in its observability layer, closes the trace span,
%%     increments the governance_executions metric, and returns the governed result.
%% (7) The agent presents the structured review (with evidence trail and categorized findings) to the human.
%% (8) The human validates and decides whether to merge. The agent never takes that action.
